{
  "texts": [
    "However, it is important to acknowledge that embedded dictionaries and biases may introduce exceptions that cannot be completely avoided.",
    "Nonetheless, computational literary studies offer advantages such as quick interpretation, analysis, and prediction on extensive datasets (Kim and Klinger, 2018).",
    "Natural language processing (NLP) techniques have been widely adopted for text classification, which assigns labels to sentences, paragraphs, or documents (Abadah et al., 2023; Asri et al., 2022; Chu et al., 2022; Fasha et al., 2022; Jafery et al., 2023; John and Keikhosrokiani, 2022; Al Mamun et al., 2022).",
    "This technique has been applied to a variety of fields, such as health, social science, business marketing and law.",
    "In particular, text classification has been used to uncover human activity in the past decades in the social sciences."
  ]
}